<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
        <img src="#xarTplGetImage('admin.gif','addressbook')#" class="xar-module-icon"  alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
        <h3><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
        <p><xar:mlstring>The AddressBook was inspired by the Palm V PDA and gives your site to ability to have a single, shared contact list of
      multiple private address lists for each registered user.</xar:mlstring>
      <ul>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Xaraya API / BL compliant.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Flexible categories &amp; contact labels</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Add custom fields for each entry</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Full text search</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Image support for each contact</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Quality Control Reporting</xar:mlstring></li>
      </ul>
        </p>
      <h3><xar:mlstring>User Features</xar:mlstring></h3>
       <table width="80%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
          <tr align="left" valign="top">
            <td><ul>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Each address entry can be categorized</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Up to 5 contact labels per address</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Free choice for primary contact (shown in list view)</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>The list of addresses can be narrowed by selecting an individual category</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Address record sorting can be configured multiple ways</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Unlimited optional fields</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Custom TEXTAREA field width is configurable</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Configurable main menu</xar:mlstring></li>
              </ul></td>
            <td><ul>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Free format note field for each contact</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Auto-fill company address by lookup feature</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Copy to clipboard feature (Internet Explorer only / requires Xaraya &quot;sniffer&quot; module to be installed)</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Auto-detect mail and url contact labels</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Global and/or private contacts</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Show postal code before city (International) option</xar:mlstring></li>
              </ul></td>
          </tr>
          </table>
          <h3><xar:mlstring>Administrator Notes</xar:mlstring></h3>

        <p><xar:mlstring>As an administrator you have access to all records of all users in the Address Book.
        Therefore the &quot;Show private contacts&quot; switch works different for the administrator than for other
        users. If it set to &quot;on&quot;, all records you have entered are shown, if it is set to &quot;off&quot;
        all records of all users are shown. A registered user will see only his own records marked as private.
        So if you want to test the Address Book, create a user account and log in    as a normal user.</xar:mlstring></p>
        <p><xar:mlstring>As an administrator you will always see the full main menu with all options, regardless of any setting that
        are made in</xar:mlstring> <a href="#xarModURL('addressbook','admin','modifyconfig')#">Modify Configuration</a>.</p>
        <p><xar:mlstring>For additional information consult the</xar:mlstring> <a href="#xarModURL('addressbook','admin','displaydocs')#"><xar:mlstring>Administrator Documentation</xar:mlstring></a>.</p>
